description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hospital Sterilisation Unit Assistant Worcester Royal Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time - 24 Hours per Week – between 3am and 8pm &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(Shifts to be discussed at interview)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic applicants who would like to work in the challenging and changing world of sterilisation and decontamination services within the Hospital setting. Most of our staff have been with us for many years and now due to retirements and work expansion we are hoping to recruit similar dedicated individuals to the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will assist in the collection, cleaning, inspection, packing and sterilisation of hospital medical equipment and surgical instrumentation. You will be able to work as part of a team and have a flexible approach to your work. You should also possess good verbal and written communication skills. Previous experience in a similar environment and the NHS would be desirable, however full training will be given. There may be opportunities to undertake further additional training which will lead to a nationally recognised decontamination specific qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in an on-call system will be required when six month basic training has been completed as and when required. You should be prepared to take part in a 1:5 rota system covering Saturday mornings but there will be other regular opportunities for weekend overtime.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further enquiries please contact: Stephen Steward, HSDU Manager on 01527 512076.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email address – stephen.steward@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
